         <abstract>
            <p>In numerical analysis it is important to construct interpolating polynomials approximating a given function and its derivatives simultaneously. The authors define some new good interpolating matrices with "many" nodes close to the endpoints of the interval and also give error estimates.</p>
          </abstract>
